import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About IWINNI"
	description="IWINNI is a modern media and publishing platform dedicated to global travel, outdoor adventure, and high-altitude exploration."
	pubDate={new Date('2024-01-01')}
	heroImage="/hero-about.jpg"
>
	<p>
		IWINNI is a modern media and publishing platform dedicated to global travel, outdoor adventure,
		and high-altitude exploration. We deliver highly engaging, factual, and deeply researched article
		briefs that connect passionate outdoor enthusiasts with authentic stories from the world's most
		iconic regions.
	</p>

	<p>
		From backcountry operational updates and summit dispatches to global destination insights and
		community highlights, IWINNI is the modern explorer's guide to navigating the edge of adventure.
		We believe the best stories come from people who've been there — who've felt the altitude in
		their lungs, crossed the glacial rivers, and earned the view.
	</p>

	<h2>What We Believe</h2>

	<p>
		Adventure is not a hobby — it's a lens. The way you approach a high-altitude traverse, a
		backcountry descent, or a multi-week international expedition shapes how you understand risk,
		community, and the natural world. IWINNI exists to document and amplify that perspective,
		bringing rigorous editorial standards to a space often dominated by hype over honesty.
	</p>

	<p>
		We are committed to factual, deeply sourced reporting. Every brief we publish is grounded in
		firsthand accounts, verified operational data, and genuine community insight. We don't traffic
		in clickbait. We write for people who want to understand a place deeply before they set foot in it.
	</p>

	<h2>What We Cover</h2>

	<p>
		<strong>Global Travel</strong> — Destination deep-dives, logistics intelligence, and insider
		perspectives from every corner of the globe. Whether it's navigating permit systems in the
		Dolomites or understanding the seasonal window for a Patagonian traverse, we give you the
		operational picture.
	</p>

	<p>
		<strong>Outdoor Adventure</strong> — Trail reports, gear analysis, route beta, and the
		communities that push the limits of what's possible in the backcountry. We cover the Pacific
		Crest Trail and the Appalachian Trail as rigorously as we cover remote routes in Kyrgyzstan
		or the Canadian Rockies.
	</p>

	<p>
		<strong>High-Altitude Exploration</strong> — Expedition briefings, summit condition reports,
		and the science behind extreme-altitude physiology. From 8,000-meter objectives in the
		Himalaya to technical routes in the Andes and Karakoram, we track the world's highest pursuits
		with precision and respect.
	</p>

	<h2>Our Standards</h2>

	<p>
		Every piece published on IWINNI undergoes editorial review for factual accuracy and contextual
		depth. We cite sources, credit local expertise, and acknowledge the indigenous communities and
		land stewards whose knowledge underpins the adventure tourism industry. We believe in
		responsible storytelling — inspiring readers while acknowledging the environmental and cultural
		weight of the places we cover.
	</p>

	<p>
		Follow our journey on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/iwinni" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
		and join a community of explorers who take their adventures seriously.
	</p>
</Layout>
